The paper discusses recommendation systems, which are commonly studied in the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The focus on multiple stakeholders and fairness suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-categories, as these areas often deal with issues of fairness and multiple stakeholders. Finally, the mention of group recommendation suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
